%pyspark
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

sun = spark.read.parquet("hdfs:///ds/sun.parquet")
df_nt = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///ds/nt.parquet')
def getsrs(day):
    rs = sun.select("rise", "set")\
            .where('date = "%s"' % day)\
            .collect()
    return {"rise" : str(rs[0][0]),
            "set" : str(rs[0][1])}

getsrs('2018-10-28')

%pyspark
select_date = '2017-10-20'
rise = getsrs(select_date)['rise']
set = getsrs(select_date)['set']

cct = df_nt.filter('date == "%s"' % (select_date))\
        .filter('time >= "%s"' % rise)\
        .filter('time <= "%s"' % set)\
        .select('cct')\
        .toPandas().values

plt.close()

fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()
ax1.plot(np.arange(len(cct)), cct, label='cct')
ax1.set_ylim(0, (int(max(cct) / 10000) + 1) * 10000)
ax1.set_xlabel('time')
ax1.set_ylabel('cct')
plt.show()

%sql
select
    *
from nt_sel
where time > '05:11' and time < '19:53'
-- and cct < 10000
order by date, time
